{"name":"Delerium Hunt","pages":[{"sort":300000,"name":"Garmyr Hunters: Escaping the Ruins","type":"text","_id":"7amOBWErGvUwJ9Oh","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h3>As a Fight</h3><p><strong>10 / </strong>[[/r (3d6)]] @UUID[Compendium.world.dungeons-of-drakkenheim-bestiary.mCHHQH8KHZG322NG]{Garmyr} (Weakened) / @UUID[Compendium.world.dungeons-of-drakkenheim-bestiary.BF3xeCMvaVUrVptp]{Garmyr (Glaive)}</p><p><strong>2 / </strong>[[/r (1d4)]] @UUID[Compendium.world.dungeons-of-drakkenheim-bestiary.pwHF1SVV3bnhPwpX]{Wargs} (Weakened)</p><p><strong>360 XP - Extreme ++</strong></p><h3>As a Chase</h3><h4><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Run!</span></span></h4><p><strong>Chase Points: 3 Overcome:</strong> <code>DC 15 Deception</code> to create a diversion, <code>DC 17 Athletics</code> to get a head start.</p><h4><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Sneak Away</span></span></h4><p><strong>Chase Points: 4 Overcome: </strong><code>DC 17 Stealth</code> to sneak along the wall, <code>DC 15 Survival</code> to go around the other side.</p><h4><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Collapsed Wall</span></span></h4><p><strong>Chase Points: 4 Overcome:</strong> <code>DC 13 Athletics</code> to climb over, <code>DC 15 Thievery</code> to unlock a gate</p><h4><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Wrong Turn</span></span></h4><p><strong>Chase Points: 5 Overcome: </strong><code>DC 15 Nature</code> to avoid the poison flowers, <code>DC 17 Acrobatics</code> to parkour the blocked wall</p><h4><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Rickety Rooftops</span></span></h4><p><strong>Chase Points: 2 Overcome: </strong><code>DC 15 Acrobatics</code> to balance across the beam, <code>DC 13 Athletics</code> to jump from roof to roof.</p><h4><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Twisting Alleyways</span></span></h4><p><strong>Chase Points: 5 Overcome: </strong><code>DC 17 Perception Check</code> to find a path, <code>DC 13 Society</code> to recall a map.</p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":200000,"name":"Ratling Scavengers: Random Encounter","type":"text","_id":"ZacaCa4vHfC9Vc62","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><strong>10 /</strong> [[/r (3d6)]] @UUID[Compendium.world.dungeons-of-drakkenheim-bestiary.2dBXhfzVjF5lVRhV]{Ratlings} hide down a nearby alley or passage awaiting unsuspecting prey.</p><p><strong>140 XP - Extreme</strong></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":150000,"name":"Cratered Street: Successful Search","type":"text","_id":"Y95NFjP7JOdpgnJ2","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h3>Trigger</h3><p>Characters find this location once they successfully search the ruins and score two or more successful check results.</p><h3>Read</h3><p><em>This blasted street is filled with small craters. Tiny crystals glow with prismatic light within each.</em></p><h3>Encounter</h3><p>There are <strong>5</strong> @UUID[Compendium.world.dungeons-of-drakkenheim-bestiary.NxBHDItWTjosWl6q]{Haze Husks} stumbling aimlessly around the craters.</p><p><strong>150 XP - Extreme</strong></p><h3>Loot</h3><p>Characters can extract <strong>10</strong> [[/r (3d6)]] @UUID[Item.wbzwuB0wPcqiet3S]{Delerium Chips} worth <em>10gp each</em> and <strong>3</strong> [[/r (1d6)]] @UUID[Item.CwtdKFwdweGzf9Iy]{Delerium Fragments} worth <em>100gp each</em>. This takes about 10 minutes.</p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":100000,"name":"Searching The Ruins","type":"text","_id":"PaS4IYvChZ3ob6ph","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>Use these guidelines whenever the characters deliberately search for something in the ruins, such as scavenged supplies, lost treasures, unknown locations, a hidden foe, or a safe place to rest. Conducting a good search takes at least <em>one hour</em>; during which the characters may survey an area with up to 1/4 mile diameter. After one hour of searching, each character makes a <strong>Perception Check</strong> or <strong>Survival Check</strong>. <em>Exceeding the DC by 5 or more grants an additional success</em>. Whether or not the characters find anything is determined by the total number of successes:</p><ul><li><p><strong>3 or more successes:</strong> The party finds what they are looking for if it can be found within the search area, otherwise, they conclusively rule out any possibility that what they where seeking was in the area of their search.</p></li><li><p><strong>2 or more failed checks:</strong> The characters stumble into a Random Encounter, but if they still had enough successes, they also find whatever they sought.</p></li></ul><h4>Characters might use special skills when searching for something specific:</h4><ul><li><p><strong>Arcana</strong> - Delerium deposits or magical phenomena.</p></li><li><p><strong>Crafting</strong> - Searching an area the characters have visited at least once before themselves, or for artisan's and crafting supplies.</p></li><li><p><strong>Society</strong> - Specific and notable monuments, buildings, or residences.</p></li><li><p><strong>Nature</strong> - Exploring natural environments such as Queen's Park.</p></li><li><p><strong>Survival</strong> - Tracking monsters or people.</p></li><li><p><em>Stealth and Perception - Checks do not contribute to success, but may be used to evade or detect hostile threats while the characters search the ruins.</em></p></li></ul><h3>Outer City Delerium Deposits</h3><ul><li><p><strong>2 Success or Fewer:</strong> Nothing</p></li><li><p><strong>3 Successes:</strong> <strong>10</strong> [[/r (3d6)]] @UUID[Item.wbzwuB0wPcqiet3S]{Delerium Chips} worth <em>10gp each</em>.</p></li><li><p><strong>4 Successes:</strong> <strong>3</strong> [[/r (1d6)]] @UUID[Item.CwtdKFwdweGzf9Iy]{Delerium Fragments} worth <em>100gp each</em>.</p></li><li><p><strong>5 or more Successes:</strong> <strong>1</strong> @UUID[Item.IDL91tJIgEVCrImJ]{Delerium Shard} worth <em>500gp.</em></p></li></ul><p></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}}],"ownership":{"default":0,"NZsmhzO5jgDe7jrT":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.gDD0dlx03uolBfIl"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.10.4","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674952573304,"modifiedTime":1686624807725,"lastModifiedBy":"NZsmhzO5jgDe7jrT"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"C1UVSrHjT58vSEpN"}
{"name":"Rat's Nest","pages":[{"sort":100000,"name":"[1]Cratered Basement","type":"text","_id":"xXw1KMQqxLUnirnd","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><em>The stone walls of the basement are scorched and blackened. Rubble and debris surround a muddy crater fifteen feet wide and five feet deep. A faint glimmer of octarine light twinkles within.</em></p><hr /><ol><li><p>Examining the crater for the source of the glow turns up [[/r (1d6)]] @UUID[Item.wbzwuB0wPcqiet3S]{Delerium Chips} worth <em>10gp each</em>. There’s a distinct rocky divot about a foot wide just off the centre of the crater, as if a large hunk of rock was dug out and excavated. If there was a meteorite here, it’s gone now.</p></li><li><p>The ratlings removed a chunk of rock fused with a delerium crystal from the crater and dragged it into the Seer’s Den [Area 8]. A <code>Survival (DC 15)</code> check reveals drag marks, muddy tracks, and clawed footprints of several beastly creatures indicating something heavy was removed from the crater recently.</p></li><li><p><code>Perception (DC 15)</code>, or <code>Crafting (DC18)</code>. The breached wall was not caused by the meteor impact. The passage was dug relatively recently.</p></li></ol>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":0,"name":"Description Notes","type":"text","_id":"nz5a6sFjiDa5rRUQ","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h1>Ratling Burrow</h1><p>These details are common to most areas within the ratling burrows:</p><h2>Passages</h2><p>The tunnels are dug out from packed earth, clay, loose dirt, and bits of stone. The cramped passages are five to ten feet wide, and rarely more than six feet high. Medium-sized creatures must stoop throughout. The tunnels weave and bend left and right, but also up and down.</p><h2>Chambers</h2><p>The larger rooms are eight to ten feet in height. They are mostly dry past the entrance, but unrecognizable filth, bone fragments, scraps of fur and cloth, and bits of leaves and grasses lay underfoot.</p><h2>Light</h2><p>The ratlings rely on their darkvision for sight, so there are no light sources within.</p><h2>Sounds and Smells</h2><p>The air underground is humid. It reeks of rat urine and feces. The sounds of squeaking and chattering ratlings as they scrape and scurry about can be heard down the tunnels.</p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":200000,"name":"[2]Trapped Entrance Passage","type":"text","_id":"Cuea32slqkOf0aDQ","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><em>This muddy passage is roughly eight feet wide. It tunnels steeply down ten feet before veering sharply left.</em></p><hr /><ol><li><p><code>Perception (DC 14)</code>. The wet mud is slippery, and could lead to a nasty fall.</p></li><li><p>Muddy Slide - Characters without a climbing speed travelling down the entrance passage must succeed on a <code>Reflex Save (DC 17)</code> or slip on the muddy slide. Characters can use a rope to gain a +2 circumstance bonus to this save.</p></li><li><p>Characters who fail this save fall prone and immediately slide down the passage, where they are deposited into the @UUID[Actor.9THpC9FlaqnidfvS]{Spiked Pit} in the Lookout’s Burrow [Area 3].</p></li></ol>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":300000,"name":"[3]Lookout's Burrow","type":"text","_id":"AwX4jcba35GM44yH","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><em>The sound of soft rustling and chittering rats fills this muddy earthen den.</em></p><hr /><h2>Ratlings</h2><p><strong>2 </strong>@UUID[Compendium.world.dungeons-of-drakkenheim-bestiary.gKrainSURCxxtdzs]{Ratling Guttersnipes} and <strong>6</strong> @UUID[Compendium.world.dungeons-of-drakkenheim-bestiary.2dBXhfzVjF5lVRhV]{Ratlings} are on watch. Each carries a crossbow and a few prepared flasks of @UUID[Item.JmLjQ2WYx8ROOeRy]{Alchemist's Fire (Lesser)}.</p><p><strong>150 XP - Extreme</strong></p><h2>Hazards</h2><p>A @UUID[Actor.9THpC9FlaqnidfvS]{Spiked Pit} ten feet deep is dug in the ground at the base of the Trapped Entrance Passage [Area 2]. The hole is covered by a large cloth anchored on the pit’s edge and camouflaged with mud and debris. The pit has a <code>Stealth DC 20</code>. Anyone who moves onto the cloth falls into the pit onto the sharpened wooden spikes at the bottom, and takes [[/r 10[bludgeoning]]] damage plus [[/r 2d6[piercing]]] damage from sharp implements at the bottom of the pit. That creature can use the @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.3yoajuKjwHZ9ApUY]{Grab an Edge} reaction to avoid falling. The edges of the pit are slippery, making escape difficult.</p><p><strong>8 XP - Simple Hazard</strong></p><h4><strong>1</strong> @UUID[Actor.L3IrW0NIXwM1PLNR]{Rat Swarm} lives at the bottom of the pit, and begins devouring anyone who falls within. The swarm attacks any creature in the pit as food.</h4><p><strong>30 XP</strong></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":400000,"name":"[4]Ratling Nests","type":"text","_id":"Pc1GLEii0to695QG","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><em>This tiny dugout cavity contains a cup-shaped nest made from long grasses, hay, mud, twigs, and leaves, and is lined with shredded bits of discarded cloth, fur scraps, bits of leather, paper, and small glimmering trinkets.</em></p><hr /><h2>Ratlings</h2><p><strong>8</strong> @UUID[Actor.08NJh0E1fF7xBAVb]{Ratlings} and <strong>1</strong> @UUID[Actor.uwOFfgK6ThOP5hE2]{Ratling Guttersnipe} are present in each nest cluster, scattered across the individual nest cavities.</p><p><strong>150 XP - Extreme</strong></p><h2>Treasure</h2><p>Ratlings hoard small trinkets as personal treasure, plus a @UUID[Item.wbzwuB0wPcqiet3S]{Delerium Chip} or a pouch of <em>10gp</em>. One nest contains a @UUID[Item.b2inhv5Tc168ZIzZ]{Healing Potion (Minor)}.</p><p></p><p></p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":500000,"name":"[5]Food Caches","type":"text","_id":"6Xnl57AGMzd5Ws1J","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><em>Haphazardly splayed about this rancid-smelling den are all manner of recently-scavenged dead animals, body parts, and other unsavoury stores.</em></p><hr /><ul><li><p>Living meat stays well-preserved, so occasionally prisoners are tied up here for a fresh meal later.</p></li></ul><h2>North Cache</h2><ul><li><p>The north cache contains @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.equipment-srd.zvLyCVD8g2PdHJAc]{Thieves' Tools}, @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.equipment-srd.SGkOHFyBbzWdBk8D]{Healer's Tools (Expanded)}, @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.equipment-srd.4ftXXUCBHcf4b0MH]{Alchemist's Tools}, @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.equipment-srd.YhkomhtKBK3i9C7Q]{Disguise Kit (Elite)}, @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.equipment-srd.9UJbMaglf35GVzaZ]{Climbing Kit}, and a @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.equipment-srd.zC7LipQPHRYw2RXx]{Barkskin Potion}.</p></li></ul><h2>South Cache</h2><ul><li><p>The south cache holds a still-living captive prisoner - <strong>Petra Lang</strong> of the <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Hooded Lanterns</span> (an urban ranger). She is unarmed, wounded (with 20 hp remaining), and has expended all her spell slots. However, she’s willing to help fight her way out if provided a weapon. Characters can recognize her as a Hooded Lantern lieutenant by her cloak and garb. If she survives, she asks the characters to help her get back to Shepherd’s Gate. She can make the trip on her own, but wants the characters to meet her comrades.</p></li></ul>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":600000,"name":"[6]Idol of the Rat God","type":"text","_id":"kVT4FNK0CeLPL0AB","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><em>This chamber contains a bloated effigy of a horrifically obese demonic rat made from rubble, mud, and rat feces, set with two pieces of delerium for eyes. Offerings are scattered about the statue’s feet — skulls, bone, daggers, bits of rotting meat, and smaller delerium fragments. Before it lies a blood-soaked altar made from a simple stone slab.</em></p><hr /><h2>Fleeing Ratlings</h2><p><strong>6</strong> @UUID[Actor.08NJh0E1fF7xBAVb]{Ratlings} attend the shrine. They flee for help if intruders arrive here.</p><p><strong>90 XP - Moderate</strong></p><h2>Treasure</h2><p>The eyes of the idol are @UUID[Item.CwtdKFwdweGzf9Iy]{Delerium Fragments} worth <em>100 gp each</em>. [[/r (1d6)]] @UUID[Item.wbzwuB0wPcqiet3S]{Delerium Chips} worth <em>10gp each</em> are scattered about the altar. Several scrolls are placed at the altar here — @UUID[Item.Q2SxLOMHI88yxub6]{Scroll of Bane (Level 1)}, @UUID[Item.YXUskVb381iJ5L8X]{Scroll of Faerie Fire (Level 2)}, and @UUID[Item.C3JL4TRTgoAYwNzX]{Scroll of Harm (Level 2)}.</p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":700000,"name":"[7]Gathering Den","type":"text","_id":"JghOunyushAAdqAL","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><em>Bales of hay and animal skins surround a glowing bonfire in this large foetid chamber.</em></p><hr /><ol><li><p><strong>The</strong> @UUID[Compendium.world.dungeons-of-drakkenheim-bestiary.8IFIjqpJ32hBMFty]{Rat Prince} is often found here carousing with six other @UUID[Compendium.world.dungeons-of-drakkenheim-bestiary.2dBXhfzVjF5lVRhV]{Ratlings}.</p><p><strong>150 XP - Extreme</strong></p></li><li><p>This burrow tunnel opens into the sewers. The ratlings flee here and scatter if they are wounded or cannot defend their lair.</p></li></ol>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":800000,"name":"[8]Seer's Den","type":"text","_id":"dB3GQhHs4glBSRwQ","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p><em>In this spacious chamber is a large and sumptuous basket nest. Woven over the nest is a canvas made from stitched together scraps of fine cloth, twigs, and choice leaves. Before the nest is a rough stone plinth upon which is placed a hunk of silvery rock about a foot wide. A protruding delerium crystal is embedded in its surface.</em></p><hr /><ol><li><p>@UUID[Compendium.world.dungeons-of-drakkenheim-bestiary.BFZLAI30cG605uQm]{Squeaks the Seer} keeps her nest here. She has an imp familiar who remains in rat form. In its true form, it resembles a disgusting winged and hairless rat.</p><p><strong>90 XP - Moderate</strong></p></li><li><p>The @UUID[Item.CA8iYWNULHrVqKKx]{Delerium Crystal} is here! It’s still stuck in a rocky chunk: a combination of stone from the tavern basement, melted earth, and meteoric rock. The Ratlings dislodged it and brought it here because they couldn’t break the crystal from the rock themselves. The chunk of rock weighs about fifty pounds.</p></li></ol>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}}],"ownership":{"default":0,"NZsmhzO5jgDe7jrT":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.gtPUOTnU4M3HSyXA"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.10.4","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1676675042992,"modifiedTime":1686624819801,"lastModifiedBy":"NZsmhzO5jgDe7jrT"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"LwhNWM3RVDYtcDtp"}
{"name":"Town Map","pages":[{"sort":100000,"name":"Town Map","type":"image","_id":"kDjHs3C420anNmpi","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{"caption":"Labeled in Emma Crowe's own handwriting."},"text":{"format":1},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":"modules/drakkenheim-adventure-module-for-pathfinder-2nd-edition/maps/Map_of_Emberwood_Labeled.webp","system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}}],"ownership":{"default":3,"NZsmhzO5jgDe7jrT":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.oL236Uj5uTOdQuY9"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.10.4","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1673670787473,"modifiedTime":1686958622294,"lastModifiedBy":"NZsmhzO5jgDe7jrT"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"q6T8AypaDbKnIf9O"}
